<title>USA: NYS Senate passes bill creating NYC bonding agency.</title>
<headline>NYS Senate passes bill creating NYC bonding agency.</headline>
<dateline>ALBANY, N.Y. 1997-02-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>The New York State Senate passed a bill that would create a new, temporary bonding authority for New York City.</p>
<p>The measure would allow the city to bypass a debt cap and sell up to $7.5 billion of bonds. The state Assembly is now voting on the measure and is expected to pass it, according to Assembly Speaker Sheldon Silver.</p>
<p>((--U.S. Municipal Desk, 212-859-1650))</p>
